Guterres wrote to Kabila to propose a joint visit with African Union (AU) Chairperson Moussa Faki Mahamat following a series of meetings he held on the sidelines of the AU summit in Addis Ababa in late January. There is growing international concern that the DRC could slide into all-out violence as it heads to elections on December 23. "I can confirm that a letter was sent and that a message came back that they would be welcome in Kinshasa at their earliest convenience," the UN Spokesperson Stephane Dujarric told AFP. No date has been set for the visit. --AFP--